    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Maps having decorative panels of views, monuments, costumed figures, or other illustrations that surround the actual cartographic representation. Illustrations were often arranged around the borders, particularly in early examples from the 16th and 17th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
